# Prompt 027: Diagram Hand-drawn Style & Shape Categories (P2)

## Objective
Add Excalidraw-style hand-drawn/sketchy rendering mode and additional shape categories to provide aesthetic variety and support informal diagram styles.

## Context
- **Feature:** Diagrams (P2 - Style and shape variety)
- **Current State:** Professional diagrams with templates, auto-layout, layers, 70+ shapes
- **Gaps:**
  1. No hand-drawn/sketchy rendering style (all shapes are crisp/geometric)
  2. Limited shape categories (could expand flowchart, UML, cloud, etc.)
- **Priority:** P2 - Aesthetic variety, not critical for core diagramming

## Requirements

### Part 1: Hand-drawn Rendering Style

#### 1.1 Style Toggle
**Purpose:** Switch between crisp and hand-drawn rendering

**Implementation:**
```typescript
// In src/stores/useDiagramEditorStore.ts
interface DiagramState {
  // ... existing fields
  renderStyle: 'crisp' | 'hand-drawn'; // NEW
  setRenderStyle: (style: 'crisp' | 'hand-drawn') => void;
}

// In src/components/DiagramCanvas/Toolbar.tsx
<button
  onClick={() => setRenderStyle(renderStyle === 'crisp' ? 'hand-drawn' : 'crisp')}
  className={/* active when hand-drawn */}
  title="Toggle hand-drawn style"
>
  <Pencil className="w-4 h-4" />
  {renderStyle === 'hand-drawn' ? 'Hand-drawn' : 'Crisp'}
</button>
```

#### 1.2 Rough.js Integration
**Purpose:** Render shapes with sketchy, hand-drawn appearance

**Dependencies:**
```bash
npm install roughjs
```

**Implementation:**
```typescript
// In src/components/DiagramCanvas/ShapeRenderer.tsx
import rough from 'roughjs';

const renderShape = (shape: DiagramShape, renderStyle: 'crisp' | 'hand-drawn') => {
  if (renderStyle === 'crisp') {
    // Existing Konva rendering
    return renderCrispShape(shape);
  }

  // Hand-drawn rendering with Rough.js
  const rc = rough.canvas(canvasElement);

  switch (shape.type) {
    case 'rectangle':
      return rc.rectangle(
        shape.x,
        shape.y,
        shape.width,
        shape.height,
        {
          roughness: 1.5, // Amount of jitter
          bowing: 2, // Curve amount
          stroke: shape.stroke,
          strokeWidth: shape.strokeWidth,
          fill: shape.fill,
          fillStyle: 'hachure', // Sketchy fill pattern
        }
      );

    case 'circle':
      return rc.circle(
        shape.x + shape.width / 2,
        shape.y + shape.height / 2,
        Math.min(shape.width, shape.height),
        {
          roughness: 1.5,
          bowing: 2,
          stroke: shape.stroke,
          strokeWidth: shape.strokeWidth,
          fill: shape.fill,
          fillStyle: 'hachure',
        }
      );

    case 'arrow':
      return rc.line(
        shape.x,
        shape.y,
        shape.endX,
        shape.endY,
        {
          roughness: 1.2,
          bowing: 1,
          stroke: shape.stroke,
          strokeWidth: shape.strokeWidth,
        }
      );

    // ... other shapes
  }
};
```

#### 1.3 Configurable Roughness
**Purpose:** Adjust hand-drawn intensity

**Implementation:**
```typescript
// In src/stores/useDiagramEditorStore.ts
interface DiagramState {
  renderStyle: 'crisp' | 'hand-drawn';
  roughness: number; // 0.5 - 3.0 (NEW)
  setRoughness: (value: number) => void;
}

// In Toolbar (shown when renderStyle === 'hand-drawn'):
<label className="flex items-center gap-2">
  <span className="text-xs">Roughness:</span>
  <input
    type="range"
    min="0.5"
    max="3"
    step="0.1"
    value={roughness}
    onChange={(e) => setRoughness(parseFloat(e.target.value))}
    className="w-24"
  />
  <span className="text-xs">{roughness.toFixed(1)}</span>
</label>
```

### Part 2: Additional Shape Categories

#### 2.1 Cloud Architecture Shapes
**Purpose:** AWS/Azure/GCP icon-style shapes

**New Shapes:**
```typescript
const CLOUD_SHAPES = [
  { id: 'cloud-server', label: 'Server', icon: 'server' },
  { id: 'cloud-database', label: 'Database', icon: 'database' },
  { id: 'cloud-storage', label: 'Storage', icon: 'harddrive' },
  { id: 'cloud-function', label: 'Function', icon: 'zap' },
  { id: 'cloud-queue', label: 'Queue', icon: 'layers' },
  { id: 'cloud-api', label: 'API Gateway', icon: 'link' },
  { id: 'cloud-cdn', label: 'CDN', icon: 'globe' },
  { id: 'cloud-load-balancer', label: 'Load Balancer', icon: 'sliders' },
];

// Add to src/data/diagram-shapes.ts:
export const SHAPE_CATEGORIES = [
  // ... existing categories (Basic, Flowchart, UML, etc.)
  {
    id: 'cloud',
    label: 'Cloud Architecture',
    shapes: CLOUD_SHAPES,
  },
];
```

#### 2.2 Mind Map Shapes
**Purpose:** Organic, thought-bubble style shapes

**New Shapes:**
```typescript
